<item>
            <title>[FLINK-13386] Fix some frictions in the new default Web UI</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-13386</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;While manually testing the new WebUI I found a few frictions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;when using the UI the left panel hides unexpectedly at random moments&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;mouse wheel does not work on the logs (taskmanager, jobmanager) pane&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;the jobmanager configuration is not sorted&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;different sorting of the operators (the old UI showed the sources first)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;the drop-down list for choosing operator/tasks metrics is not sorted, which makes it super hard to screen through available metrics&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;arrow does not touch the rectangles in Chrome (see attached screenshot)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;There are also some views missing in the new UI that I personally found useful in the old UI:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;can&apos;t see watermarks for all operators at once&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;no numeric metrics (only graphs)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
